text: Jasmine is an extinct town in Adair County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. The GNIS classifies it as a populated place, but the exact location of the town site is unknown. A post office called Jasmine was established in 1880, and remained in operation until 1886. A variant name was Crawford. ==References== Category:Ghost towns in Missouri Category:Former populated places in Adair County, Missouri
title: Jasmine, Missouri
